---
import '@fontsource/inter/400.css';
import '@fontsource/inter/500.css';
import '@fontsource/inter/600.css';
import '@fontsource/inter/700.css';
import '@fontsource/instrument-serif/400.css';

import '../../styles/kit-shared.css';
import '../../styles/layout-review-hub.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>Design Judgment Kit - Local Layout Review Hub</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Local-only review hub for kit-first layout concepts. No deployment changes included."
    />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex,nofollow" />
  </head>
  <body class="layout-review-hub">
    <a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to content</a>

    <header class="site-nav">
      <div class="nav-inner">
        <a class="brand" href="#review-pack">Judgment Kit Review</a>
        <button
          type="button"
          class="menu-toggle"
          aria-expanded="false"
          aria-controls="mobile-nav"
          data-menu-toggle
        >
          Menu
        </button>
        <nav class="nav-links" aria-label="Primary">
          <a href="#review-pack">Review pack</a>
          <a href="#layout-urls">Local URLs</a>
          <a href="#compare">Comparison</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
      <nav id="mobile-nav" class="mobile-menu" data-open="false" aria-label="Mobile sections">
        <a href="#review-pack">Review pack</a>
        <a href="#layout-urls">Local URLs</a>
        <a href="#compare">Comparison</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main id="main-content" class="layout-shell">
      <section id="review-pack" aria-labelledby="review-pack-title">
        <div class="hub-intro">
          <span class="muted-chip">Local review only</span>
          <h1 id="review-pack-title">Kit-first layout exploration pack</h1>
          <p class="subhead">
            This route is your local review hub. It links to one cleaned baseline and three additional
            layout concepts, all built around practical kit usage and explicitly excluding any style-guide
            section.
          </p>
          <div class="cta-row">
            <a class="button primary" href="#layout-urls">Open local URLs</a>
            <a class="button ghost" href="#compare">Jump to comparison table</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="layout-urls" aria-labelledby="layout-urls-title">
        <h2 id="layout-urls-title">Local URLs</h2>
        <p class="intro">Each concept has a dedicated route for isolated local review.</p>
        <div class="layout-grid">
          <article class="layout-link-card">
            <span class="muted-chip">Balanced narrative</span>
            <h3>Baseline (kit-refined)</h3>
            <p>Keeps current structure, removes style-guide content, and adds explicit kit modules.</p>
            <p><strong>Optimizes:</strong> Continuity with minimal IA change</p>
            <a href="/layouts/baseline">/layouts/baseline</a>
          </article>
          <article class="layout-link-card">
            <span class="muted-chip">Dashboard posture</span>
            <h3>Kit Workbench</h3>
            <p>Front-loads module cards and operational checklists for fast decision-oriented scanning.</p>
            <p><strong>Optimizes:</strong> Weekly operating usability</p>
            <a href="/layouts/kit-workbench">/layouts/kit-workbench</a>
          </article>
          <article class="layout-link-card">
            <span class="muted-chip">Stage-driven</span>
            <h3>Kit Flow</h3>
            <p>Maps judgment checkpoints directly to delivery phases from frame to audit.</p>
            <p><strong>Optimizes:</strong> When-to-use clarity</p>
            <a href="/layouts/kit-flow">/layouts/kit-flow</a>
          </article>
          <article class="layout-link-card">
            <span class="muted-chip">Cadence-first</span>
            <h3>Kit Ops Deck</h3>
            <p>Uses a side rail and cadence deck to emphasize ongoing rituals and role accountability.</p>
            <p><strong>Optimizes:</strong> Operations discipline</p>
            <a href="/layouts/kit-ops-deck">/layouts/kit-ops-deck</a>
          </article>
          <article class="layout-link-card">
            <span class="muted-chip">Governance prototype</span>
            <h3>Contract Workbench</h3>
            <p>Shows a governed AI UI decision record, per-test drift evidence, and escalation output.</p>
            <p><strong>Optimizes:</strong> Contract-driven review clarity</p>
            <a href="/layouts/contract-workbench">/layouts/contract-workbench</a>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="compare" aria-labelledby="compare-title">
        <h2 id="compare-title">Quick comparison table</h2>
        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table class="data-table" aria-describedby="compare-title">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Route</th>
                <th scope="col">IA emphasis</th>
                <th scope="col">Scanning style</th>
                <th scope="col">Review posture</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">/layouts/baseline</th>
                <td>Balanced narrative + modules</td>
                <td>Linear</td>
                <td>Low-change continuity check</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">/layouts/kit-workbench</th>
                <td>Module-first dashboard</td>
                <td>Fast scan and action</td>
                <td>Operational usability check</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">/layouts/kit-flow</th>
                <td>Stage-based workflow rail</td>
                <td>Top-down by delivery phase</td>
                <td>Timing and sequence check</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">/layouts/kit-ops-deck</th>
                <td>Cadence + side-rail modules</td>
                <td>Ritual-oriented</td>
                <td>Governance and role clarity check</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">/layouts/contract-workbench</th>
                <td>Decision record + drift evidence</td>
                <td>Structured inspection</td>
                <td>Governed workflow prototype check</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <div class="review-notes">
          <p>No route includes an irrelevant visual-guidelines section.</p>
          <p>All concept routes retain search, carousel, mobile nav, and responsive table/card behavior.</p>
          <p>Contract workbench intentionally uses the flattened public styling language rather than adding new chrome.</p>
          <p>No deployment workflow was changed; this is local review only.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <footer>
        <p>Generated for local concept review. Deploy decision intentionally deferred.</p>
      </footer>
    </main>

    <script>
      import { initKitPage } from '../../scripts/init-kit-page';

      initKitPage();
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
